casebody.data:
Robert DAVIS and Desmond White, Plaintiffs-Appellants,
and
Andrew A. Paterson, Appellant,
v.
WAYNE COUNTY CLERK, Wayne County Election Commission, Detroit City Clerk, and Penelope Bailer, Defendants-Appellees. SC: 158586
COA: 339200 Supreme Court of Michigan. July 29, 2019

Order

On order of the Court, the application for leave to appeal the September 11, 2018 judgment of the Court of Appeals is considered, and it is DENIED, because we are not persuaded that the questions presented should be reviewed by this Court.
